1. DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

1.1 "Authorized User" means an individual who is authorized by You to use the
    Software pursuant to a valid License Key.

1.2 "Documentation" means any user guides, technical documentation, API references,
    and other materials provided with or related to the Software.

1.3 "License Key" means the unique alphanumeric code provided by KyotoTech that
    enables the use of the Software under a specific License Tier.

1.4 "License Tier" means the specific level of license (Free, Basic, Standard,
    Pro, or Enterprise) that determines the scope of permitted use.

1.5 "Machine" means a single physical or virtual computing device on which the
    Software is installed and activated.

1.6 "Application" means the software product developed by the Licensee that
    incorporates or uses the Software.

1.7 "Effective Date" means the date on which You first install, access, or
    otherwise use the Software, or the date on which You accept this Agreement,
    whichever occurs first.

1.8 "Intellectual Property Rights" means all patents, copyrights, trade secrets,
    trademarks, trade names, moral rights, rights of attribution, and all other
    intellectual property rights recognized in any jurisdiction worldwide.

1.9 "Confidential Information" means any non-public information about the
    Software, including but not limited to source code, algorithms, architecture,
    internal documentation, security mechanisms, encryption keys, and licensing
    infrastructure.

