================================================================================

2.1 GRANT. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement and payment of
    applicable fees, KyotoTech grants You a limited, non-exclusive,
    non-transferable, non-sublicensable, revocable license to:

    (a) Install and use the Software on the number of Machines permitted by Your
        License Tier;
    (b) Integrate the Software into Your Applications;
    (c) Distribute the Software as part of Your compiled Applications to Your
        end users, provided that the Software is not separately extractable or
        independently usable by such end users;
    (d) Use the Documentation in connection with Your permitted use of the
        Software.

2.2 FREE LICENSE. If You are using the Software under a Free License:

    (a) The Free License is perpetual and does not expire;
    (b) RSA encryption is available with limited key sizes;
    (c) Password hashing is available with watermark applied to output;
    (d) AES encryption, quantum-safe encryption, and digital signatures
        require a paid License Tier;
    (e) Free use is permitted for both evaluation and production purposes;
    (f) The Free License is provided for individual developers and small projects;
    (g) To access additional features, You may upgrade to a paid License Tier.

2.3 LICENSE TIERS. The specific permissions, limitations, and features available
    to You depend on Your License Tier. Details of each tier are available on the
    KyotoTech website. KyotoTech reserves the right to modify tier specifications
    at any time.

2.4 ACTIVATION. The Software requires license activation, which may involve:

    (a) Online activation connecting to KyotoTech licensing servers;
    (b) Hardware binding to the Machine on which the Software is activated;
    (c) Signature-based validation for mobile platforms;
    (d) Periodic validation of the license status.

    You agree to allow the Software to communicate with KyotoTech servers for
    license validation, activation, and usage tracking purposes.

