10. TERM AND TERMINATION
================================================================================

10.1 TERM. This Agreement is effective from the Effective Date and shall remain
     in force until terminated in accordance with this Section.

10.2 TERMINATION BY KYOTOTECH. KyotoTech may terminate this Agreement
     immediately upon written notice if:

     (a) You breach any term of this Agreement and fail to cure such breach
         within fifteen (15) days after receiving written notice thereof;
     (b) You breach any term of Section 3 (Restrictions) or Section 5
         (Confidentiality), which shall constitute a material breach not
         subject to cure;
     (c) You become insolvent, file for bankruptcy, or have a receiver
         appointed for Your assets;
     (d) You cease to conduct business in the normal course.

10.3 TERMINATION BY LICENSEE. You may terminate this Agreement at any time by:

     (a) Ceasing all use of the Software;
     (b) Permanently deleting all copies of the Software from all Machines;
     (c) Destroying all Documentation and related materials in Your possession.

10.4 EFFECT OF TERMINATION. Upon termination of this Agreement:

     (a) All licenses granted herein shall immediately terminate;
     (b) You must immediately cease all use of the Software;
     (c) You must permanently delete all copies of the Software from all
         Machines and systems;
     (d) You must destroy all copies of the Documentation;
     (e) You must certify in writing to KyotoTech that You have complied with
         the foregoing obligations;
     (f) KyotoTech may remotely deactivate Your License Key.

10.5 SURVIVAL. Sections 3 (Restrictions), 4 (Intellectual Property),
     5 (Confidentiality), 7 (Warranty Disclaimer), 8 (Limitation of Liability),
     9 (Indemnification), 11 (Dispute Resolution), and 12 (General Provisions)
     shall survive any termination or expiration of this Agreement.

10.6 NO REFUNDS. Except as required by applicable law, all license fees are
     non-refundable upon termination, regardless of the reason for termination.

